<br>
If you would like to get in touch with us please feel free to email us (<a href="mailto:senchainsights@swarmonline.com" target="_self" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">senchainsights@swarmonline.com</a>) or message us on Twitter (<a href="https://twitter.com/SenchaInsights" target="_self" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">@SenchaInsights</a>).</span></em><br>
<br>
&nbsp;
<h1 style="color: #9ac864;display: block;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: 30px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 100%;letter-spacing: normal;margin-top: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 10px;margin-left: 0;text-align: left;">Sencha Official</h1>

<p><a href="https://senchaevents.webex.com/mw0401l/mywebex/default.do?nomenu=true&siteurl=senchaevents&service=6&rnd=0.35116030104013674&main_url=https%3A%2F%2Fsenchaevents.webex.com%2Fec0701l%2Feventcenter%2Fevent%2FeventAction.do%3FtheAction%3Ddetail%26confViewID%3D1004618538%26%26%26%26siteurl%3Dsenchaevents" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Webinar: Re-skinning Your Apps Just Got Easier with Sencha Architect 3</a></p>

<p>Lee Boonstra will show you how to customise your applications with Sencha Architect 3 and how to export templates for use on Sencha Market. This 1 hour webinar will be extremely helpful to those looking to re-style their apps.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.sencha.com/blog/building-a-user-extension-and-integrating-it-into-sencha-architect-3-part-1/" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Building a User Extension and Integrating It Into Sencha Architect 3 (Part 1)</a></p>

<p>Aaron Conran starts a multi-part blog series describing how to build and integrate User Extensions with Sencha Architect.</p>

<hr>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h1 style="color: #9ac864;display: block;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: 30px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 100%;letter-spacing: normal;margin-top: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 10px;margin-left: 0;text-align: left;">Sponsor</h1>

